## Agent conventions

- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Keep changes minimal and focused on the current task.
- Don't add speculative error handling or future-proofing.
- When in doubt about a pattern, look at nearby code rather than importing new conventions.

## Hooks (Claude-only)

Claude Code supports `PreToolUse` hooks that run a command before a tool fires
and block the tool when the command exits non-zero. The toolkit recommends one
optional hook: a **secret-pattern poka-yoke** on `Write` and `Edit` that scans
the about-to-be-written content for known secret shapes (AWS keys, GitHub
tokens, JWTs, private-key blocks). See `GOTCHAS.md` "Secret Patterns
(recommended for hooks)" for the regex set.

This hook is **opt-in**. `/repo-onboarding` will offer to enable it and write
the config to `.claude/settings.json`. The corresponding flag in
`.claude/project.json` is `pipeline.poka_yoke: true`.

Schema (lives in `.claude/settings.json`, standard Claude Code hook format):

```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Write|Edit",
        "hooks": [
          { "type": "command", "command": "scripts/hooks/secret-scan.sh" }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

The hook script reads the tool input from stdin (JSON, includes file path and
content), greps for the secret patterns, and exits non-zero (with a message on
stderr) when a match is found. A non-zero exit blocks the `Write`/`Edit`.

**Copilot has no equivalent.** GitHub Copilot does not expose a PreToolUse-style
hook. For Copilot consumers, the only secret defense is the Stage 6 gitleaks
scan in `/sdlc` (Tier A A3) at commit time. Plan accordingly if you rely on
Copilot for production-bound work.

## Toolkit skills available

This repo uses the **brainstorm-toolkit** plugin. Available slash commands (see `.claude/skills/` or `.github/skills/` depending on your agent):

- `/brainstorm [topic]` — conversational ideation *(Plan mode on Claude, linear on Copilot)*
- `/task "description"` — create a task and execute it with TDD
- `/status` — show current task counts from TASKS.md
- `/sdlc {plan_file}` — autonomous plan-to-PR pipeline *(Claude only)*
- `/repo-onboarding` — regenerate project.json / AGENTS.md / GOTCHAS.md
- `/test-check` — run configured tests + log audit
- `/gotcha [entry]` — view or append project pitfalls
- `/eval-harness [feature]` — run pytest + fixture evals
- `/flowsim {plan}` — trace claimed flows through code and flag mismatches
- `/dead-code-review` — multi-agent dead code scan *(Claude only)*
